<br>
This is similar to my idea of giving wizards a buff line that is similar to the focus effect items(and stacks with them)(like the shaman potions).<br>
<br>
This was quickly shot down by the we don't want to buff crowd <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I really don't see how you can give the &quot;no buffs&quot; wizard what they want without redesigning zones(unsnarable, unrootable, summoning mobs) or increasing their soloablity(more mana regen, indoor standing med). I've seen clever ways to get round having to cast buffs(make the familar effect the group) but thats really just buffing without the hassle. <p>Tyron</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=myztic>MyztiC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Born-Again Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 1100<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 8:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: idea</span><hr size=1> Someone posted that they wait for mob to drop 40% of HP before nuking. Which I find funny. I generally wait till mob is 98% or 99% and start nuking... then again, so do my guildmates and thus wizards get nice damage potential on raids.<br>
<br>
As to grouping... I'm in the 'no buffs for us' - crowd. If I want to buff, I'll log in my enchanter or cleric, wizards are about dealing damage and in that we (imo) do well. In groups and in raids. But that's just my opinion.<br>
<br>
According to some posters wizards haven't been wanted in groups in last 4+ years. If that were so, how come there are so many 65th level wizards? I'm pretty sure they didn't solo their way up there. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=natanmagus>Natan Magus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1066<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 8:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> No buffs please, i am already pissed that i have to buff myself every 3 seconds with the E'ci Focus.<br>
<br>
No buffs, no pet, only damage! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twick>twick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 11:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> A few thoughts:<br>
<br>
The imbue weapons would be more in the line of an enchanter. Or the adding damage more like a mage. I like the ideas though, I think they are original <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Here are a few ideas for spells....<br>
<br>
People forget we have one of the best line of stuns. We could have an AE stun that stuns for say 15 secs and does a lot of damage, maybe 1200?. Make it have a short cast time but high aggro. Maybe even make it do the damage to the caster too, but not the stun. Make it have a very long recast time (5mins or whatever) and use a lot of mana.<br>
<br>
Another idea would be a sort of burst damage &quot;dot&quot;. Instead of being a normal dot, have it have like a countdown (30 secs or something) and after that period of time have it do the damage in one go. This way you get a mana free nuke (as you casted it 30 secs before)(unresistable maybe?) and can nuke while the timer is going down or whatever. This would increase our damage by a lot.<br>
<br>
Also (dreaming a little here hehe) we could get some &quot;real&quot; (intra zone) ports. Hell we were the masters of transport too before Luclin. Make your group, distribuited all around Norrath, Pop and Luclin, come to you. Or go to them. Lets have a second bind point, or lets be able to xloc to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>our</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> bind. Lets have a random zone port (this would be fun! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), but we still have to be better transporters than PoP books. How does this affect group? Easier gathering, easier disbanding. Not much usefulness besides that, but it would still be worth having.<br>
<br>
Group Harvest, group Familiar. Maybe the group harvest would be too much like a necro, but hey its not tapping.<br>
<br>
Clerics get this really cool spell that makes everybody's health in group go to the same percentage. Why not make a big boom using some of the groupies mana? the more mana the group has, the bigger the boom is. Make the nuke use 1 mana and have low aggro, but long recast time.<br>
<br>
Hey maybe even a slow....<br>
<br>
Just some random ideas I have, please say whatever heh.<br>
<br>
Eliocus Electrosphere<br>
Arcanist of Vazaelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lornick65>Lornick65</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/24/03 12:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> &quot;Lets have a second bind point, or lets be able to xloc to our bind&quot;<br>
